{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Ensembles"}],"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"17.0"},{"beta":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"14.0"},{"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"17.0"},{"name":"watchOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.0"}],"role":"article","title":"SwiftData Integration"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsemblesSwiftData"},{"type":"text","text":" module provides SwiftData-native APIs for Ensembles sync. Under the hood it converts SwiftData "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Model"},{"type":"text","text":" types to Core Data models and delegates to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":", but you never need to touch Core Data directly."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Quick Start with SwiftDataEnsembleContainer","anchor":"Quick-Start-with-SwiftDataEnsembleContainer"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The easiest way to add sync is with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsembleContainer"},{"type":"text","text":". It creates a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContainer"},{"type":"text","text":", sets up auto-sync, and handles the delegate:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import EnsemblesSwiftData","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","let container = SwiftDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MainStore\",","    storeURL: storeURL,","    modelTypes: [Item.self, Tag.self],","    cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","        ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.yourcompany.yourapp\"","    )",")","","\/\/ Use container.modelContainer with SwiftUI","ContentView()","    .modelContainer(container!.modelContainer)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The container auto-syncs on save, on app activation, and on a timer. Configure this with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EnsembleContainerConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    autoSyncPolicy: [.onSave, .onTimer],","    timerInterval: 60",")","let container = SwiftDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MainStore\",","    storeURL: storeURL,","    modelTypes: [Item.self],","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS,","    configuration: config",")"]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Global Identifiers with `Syncable`","anchor":"Global-Identifiers-with-Syncable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When two devices independently create the “same” object (e.g., a tag with the same name), Ensembles needs a way to recognize they represent the same entity and merge them instead of duplicating. This is called "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"deduplication","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and requires a global identifier.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftData models declare a global identifier by conforming to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol:"}]},{"code":["@Model","class Tag: Syncable {","    static let globalIdentifierKey = \"name\"","    var name: String","    \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"globalIdentifierKey"},{"type":"text","text":" names a property whose value uniquely identifies the object across all devices. When two objects of the same entity have the same global identifier value, Ensembles merges them into one."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Not all entities need global identifiers — only those where independent creation of “the same” object is likely (reference data, categories, user profiles, etc.). Entities that are always created explicitly by the user (notes, photos, messages) typically don’t need them."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Advanced: SwiftDataEnsembleDelegate","level":3,"anchor":"Advanced-SwiftDataEnsembleDelegate"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For cases where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":" isn’t sufficient — such as compound identifiers or conditional logic — use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsembleDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["class MySyncDelegate: SwiftDataEnsembleDelegate {","    func swiftDataEnsemble(","        _ ensemble: SwiftDataEnsemble,","        globalIdentifiersForManagedObjects objects: [NSManagedObject]","    ) -> [String?] {","        objects.map { object in","            guard object.entity.name == \"Item\" else { return nil }","            let first = object.value(forKey: \"firstName\") as? String ?? \"\"","            let last = object.value(forKey: \"lastName\") as? String ?? \"\"","            return \"\\(first).\\(last)\"","        }","    }","}","","let ensemble = SwiftDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    modelTypes: [Item.self],","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")","ensemble?.delegate = MySyncDelegate()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An explicit delegate takes priority over "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Using SwiftDataEnsemble Directly","level":3,"anchor":"Using-SwiftDataEnsemble-Directly","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you manage your own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" or need more control, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":" directly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let ensemble = SwiftDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    modelTypes: [Item.self, Tag.self],","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")","","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()","try await ensemble?.sync()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Access the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble"},{"text":" via the ","type":"text"},{"code":".ensemble","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property for advanced operations:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["ensemble?.ensemble.compatibilityMode = .ensembles2Compatible"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Model Versioning with VersionedSchema","type":"heading","anchor":"Model-Versioning-with-VersionedSchema"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When your SwiftData model evolves, supply all versions via a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SchemaMigrationPlan"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let ensemble = SwiftDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    migrationPlan: MyMigrationPlan.self,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles extracts each "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VersionedSchema"},{"type":"text","text":" and uses the models for version compatibility checking during sync. This ensures that events from older peers (using an earlier schema) are recognized and handled correctly."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Persistent History Tracking","anchor":"Persistent-History-Tracking"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":" enables persistent history tracking by default via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"defaultPersistentStoreOptions"},{"type":"text","text":". This allows SwiftData to detect changes that Ensembles merges into the store, so your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Query"},{"type":"text","text":" properties and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContext"},{"type":"text","text":" stay up to date automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you provide custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"persistentStoreOptions"},{"text":", make sure to include these keys:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let options: [String: Any] = [","    NSPersistentHistoryTrackingKey: true as NSNumber,","    NSPersistentStoreRemoteChangeNotificationPostOptionKey: true as NSNumber,","    \/\/ ... your other options","]"]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ensembles\/swiftdataintegration"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/ConflictResolution"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sync SwiftData models with Ensembles using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataEnsembleContainer"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SwiftDataIntegration"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsemble":{"abstract":[{"text":"The central class of Ensembles, representing a set of synchronizing persistent stores.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CoreDataEnsemble","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemble","role":"symbol","title":"CoreDataEnsemble","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CoreDataEnsemble","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/ConflictResolution":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Understand how Ensembles resolves conflicts and how to customize the process.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/ConflictResolution","role":"article","type":"topic","title":"Conflict Resolution","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/conflictresolution"},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/GettingStarted":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Getting Started","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/gettingstarted","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/GettingStarted","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up Ensembles to sync a Core Data persistent store across devices."}],"role":"article"},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles":{"abstract":[{"text":"Sync Core Data stores across devices using event sourcing.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"Ensembles","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles","type":"topic"}}}